        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "What types of leads does WhatConverts track?",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "WhatConverts tracks phone calls, form submissions, and live chat conversations. Each lead is automatically tied to its marketing source — the specific ad, keyword, campaign, or organic page that generated it. This gives you a complete picture of which efforts drive real inquiries.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h3",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Is WhatConverts suitable for small businesses with limited budgets?",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Yes. WhatConverts offers pricing tiers that scale with your needs. For small businesses running even a modest ad budget, the attribution clarity it provides often pays for itself within the first month by revealing which campaigns waste money and which deserve more investment.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h3",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "How does WhatConverts differ from Google Analytics?",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Google Analytics tracks website behavior — page views, sessions, and conversions. WhatConverts goes deeper by capturing the full lead data (caller identity, form details, chat transcripts) and linking each lead to its exact marketing source. It's built specifically for lead attribution rather than general web analytics.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      }
